entries.description: A food service director at a school district near Chicago, Illinois was arrested for allegedly stealing over $1.5 million worth of food from the district, mostly chicken wings.

entries.title: New Mexico governor's top regulatory recruit recuses self from energy merger
entries.description: New Mexico Public Regulation Commissioner Patrick O'Connell voluntarily recused himself from decisions on a major energy merger over past conflicts of interest.

entries.title: Trump says public education taken over by ‘pink-haired communists,’ plans to give power back to parents
entries.description: Former President Trump’s education plan warns that the "major problem" is "pink-haired communists teaching our kids'" and vowed to restore power back to parents.

entries.title: R. Kelly sex-abuse charges dropped by Chicago prosecutor
entries.description: Sex-abuse charges against R. Kelly have been dropped by prosecutors in Chicago, stating justice has still been served since Kelly will likely be in prison for decades following federal convictions.

entries.title: JESSE WATTERS: Our rules, our house
entries.description: Fox News host Jesse Watters gives his take on illegal migrants in New York City and America's immigration policies on 'Jesse Watters Primetime.'

entries.title: Pat McAfee rips NFL officiating after questionable no-calls on Championship Sunday: 'I think the refs suck'
entries.description: Former NFL punter and sports personality Pat McAfee ripped officiating from Championship Sunday after some questionable calls were made, especially during the Chiefs-Bengals game.

entries.title: Philadelphia would-be carjacker shot at by licensed gun owner while attempting to steal car: police
entries.description: A Philadelphia 17-year-old opened a car door and pointed a gun at two people inside but was fired upon by one of the occupants who had a gun and was a licensed carry holder, police say.

entries.title: North Dakota bill would mandate schools show video on fetal development
entries.description: A North Dakota bill would require public schools to screen videos on fetal development as part of the state's K-12 life science curriculum.

entries.title: Unlicensed North Dakota daycare operator charged with murder in baby's death
entries.description: Patricia Wick, 48, of Carrington, North Dakota, has been charged with murder after a 5-month-old boy died at her unlicensed in-home daycare.

entries.title: Attorney for 2 Denver officers push for dismissal in shooting of stranded man
entries.description: The attorney for two Denver officers is pushing for dismissal of charges in the fatal shooting of a stranded man. The man was believed to be having a "mental health crisis."

entries.title: Greg Gutfeld: Media has made Tyre Nichols' death into a 'training thing'
entries.description: 'The Five' co-host Greg Gutfeld shares his thoughts on video footage of Memphis police officers fatally beating Tyre Nichols.

entries.title: Montana won't seek death penalty for woman involved in grandson's death
entries.description: Montana won't seek the death penalty for a woman who was involved in the killing of her 12 year old grandson. Investigators found videos of the boy being abused and denied food.

entries.title: Human rights activist warns of abuses in Congo cobalt mines: 'Moral clock dialed back to colonial times'
entries.description: Human rights activist Siddharth Kara shares the connection between cobalt, lithium-ion batteries, major companies like Apple, Tesla and Microsoft and human rights abuses.

entries.title: South Dakota GOP advances Medicaid work requirement bill
entries.description: A bill that would require Medicaid recipients to work has passed the South Dakota House's Republican-dominated State Affairs Committee.

entries.title: South Carolina Attorney General Wilson asks court to reconsider abortion ruling
entries.description: South Carolina Attorney General Alan Wilson asked the court to reconsider its ruling striking down the six-week abortion ban. Wilson filed a rehearing request with the Supreme Court.

entries.title: Mississippi senators push bill to specify lawmakers must meet in public
entries.description: Mississippi senators are pushing a bill that specifies that lawmakers must meet in public, prohibiting closed-door meetings. These meetings discuss legislative strategy and policy.

entries.title: Dallas Zoo says two emperor tamarin monkeys were taken from their enclosure
entries.description: The Dallas Zoo said Monday that two emperor tamarin monkeys were taken from their habitat, just weeks after holes were cut in enclosures for a clouded leopard and langur monkeys.

entries.title: West Point continues to impose COVID-19 vaccine mandate, despite rule's lift by Pentagon: report
entries.description: The U.S. Military Academy at West Point continues to impose COVID-19 mandates regarding unvaccinated students not being able to travel.

entries.title: Russian business magnate accused of hacking, insider trading
entries.description: Russian businessman Vladislav Klyushin has been charged in an alleged scheme to hack into U.S. computer networks for insider information on American companies.

entries.title: Florida drive-by shooting injures 10 people, police say attack was 'targeted'
entries.description: Ten people were shot Monday in Florida during a "targeted" drive-by shooting, police said.

entries.title: Pompeo highlights threat from China after Air Force general predicts war by 2025
entries.description: Threats from China and Iran should put the world on alert, Mike Pompeo said in a recent interview on Fox News Channel's "Special Report" nightly program.

entries.title: JJ Watt's cryptic tweet has NFL world wondering if he might transition to coaching
entries.description: J.J. Watt is done rushing quarterbacks and setting the edge after 12 seasons in the NFL, but what's next? Could coaching be in his future? A cryptic photo on Twitter may suggest it.

entries.title: Bob Born, candy executive and 'Father of Peeps,' dead at 98
entries.description: Ira "Bob" Born, 98, of Bethlehem, Pennsylvania, who led Just Born Quality Confections for much of his adult life and mechanized the "Peeps" manufacturing process, died Sunday.

entries.title: Iowa youth program leader injured in school shooting released from hospital
entries.description: Will Keeps, of Des Moines, Iowa, an ex-gang member who founded an educational program for at-risk youth, was released from the hospital Monday after he was wounded in a school shooting.

entries.title: Manufacturer, state of Michigan agree to $663K payout for 'forever chemicals' investigation
entries.description: A Michigan plastics manufacturer has reached an agreement with the state to subsidize an investigation into the usage of PFAS "forever chemicals" at a former factory in Livingston.

entries.title: Harvard law professor falls for fake tweet suggesting governor's child was 'immaculately conceived:' 'WTAF!?'
entries.description: Harvard law professor Laurence Tribe was widely mocked online for believing a fake tweet claiming Montana Gov. Greg Gianforte's child was 'immaculately conceived.'

entries.title: Los Angeles firefighters help deliver baby: 'They talked us through what to do'
entries.description: Two Los Angeles Firemen helped assist in the birth of Soren Longo after his mother, Astrid, went into labor three-and-a-half weeks early.

entries.title: NYC Mayor Eric Adams on Empire State Building lighting firestorm: 'That got away from us'
entries.description: New York City Mayor Eric Adams reacted to the furor of the Empire State Building lighting up green after the Philadelphia Eagles' win in the NFC Championship Game on Sunday.

entries.title: Idaho murder victim Ethan Chapin's family reflects on 'challenging time' as his siblings return to school
entries.description: Ethan Chapin's mother on Monday reflected on a 'challenging time' sending her two surviving children back to the University of Idaho after her son's murder on Nov. 13.

entries.title: Former Guatemalan police chief convicted of US visa fraud
entries.description: The former Guatemalan police chief has been convicted of lying on U.S. immigration forms regarding a prior conviction case. The 82 year old lied in order to receive a green card.

entries.title: Cindy Williams shared her faith in God: 'Power that was unconditionally good'
entries.description: The actress Cindy Williams died in Los Angeles, her family announced. Among the legacies she left the world, aside from her acting, was a belief in God that she shared in books and interviews.

entries.title: Chicago construction workers accused of stealing from burned high-rise
entries.description: Two employees of a company hired to restore a Chicago high-rise damaged in a recent fire were arrested for allegedly stealing $19,000 and jewelry from a unit in the building.

entries.title: Tennessee DA warns all involved in Tyre Nichols death more charges could come as 7th officer relieved of duty
entries.description: Shelby County, Tennessee District Attorney Steve Mulroy issued a stark warning to anyone involved in the death of Tyre Nichols, that more charges could be filed.

entries.title: Louis CK, fans slammed after he sells out Madison Square Garden: 'Keeps me up at night'
entries.description: Comedian Louis CK was slammed online after he returned to comedy at Madison Square Garden this passed weekend in front of a sold out crowd.

entries.title: Hulk Hogan 'can’t feel his lower body' after another back surgery, Kurt Angle says
entries.description: Hulk Hogan appeared on the RAW anniversary show last Monday with Jimmy Hart but Kurt Angle said 'The Hulkster' is battling some health issues.

entries.title: Tim Scott, Cory Booker still hoping for bipartisan police reform despite slim prospects
entries.description: Sens. Tim Scott and Cory Booker remain committed to negotiating for police reform following the death of Tyre Nichols, but hopes of a bill approved in both chambers are slim.

entries.title: Cindy Williams, 'Laverne & Shirley' actress, dead at 75
entries.description: Cindy Williams, the actress who starred in "Laverne & Shirley," has died after a brief illness. She was 75.

entries.title: Migrants' refusal to leave New York hotel met with outrage: 'Absolutely insane'
entries.description: Migrants protested in the streets of Hell's Kitchen after the city tried to move them to a new center at the Red Hook cruise terminal in Brooklyn, reports say.

entries.title: McCarthy spars with CBS host on election denial hypocrisy: 'Why don't you also hold Democrats' accountable
entries.description: House Speaker Kevin McCarthy sparred with CBS host Margaret Brennen on Sunday for attacking Republicans on deny election results while ignoring Democrats for doing the same.
